            "last_activity_date": 1368997793,
            "creation_date": 1368997793,
            "body": "<p>you need a main method in a java application and an init method in an applet. It's the point of entry.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 16639508,
            "question_id": 16639495
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9a0996773e6a6753eac07fbe0b090a85?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 698222,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 573032,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/573032/roman-c",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Roman C",
                "accept_rate": 77
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1462017158,
            "creation_date": 1368998089,
            "body": "<p>Html document should be in the folder where the <code>pack1<\/code>, and <code>test2.class<\/code> should be in the <code>pack1<\/code> folder. Everything should be copied to the web root folder.<\/p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-html prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;applet code=\"pack1.test2.class\"  width=\"200\" height=\"200\"&gt;&lt;/applet&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The value in the code attribute can be of the form <code>classname.class<\/code> or of the form <code>packagename.classname.class<\/code>. See <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/technotes/guides/jweb/applet/applet_dev_guide.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Applet Developer's Guide<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 16639551,
            "question_id": 16639495,
            "last_edit_date": 1462017158
        }
